'''Ural-Altaic'''
# A hypothetical [[grouping]] consisting of the two language families known as [[Uralic]] and [[Altaic]], implying their genetic relationship. Since the term describes a theoretical grouping that remains conjectural due to a lack of clear evidence, the grouping lacks recognition among most comparative linguists today who prefer to treat [[Uralic]] and [[Altaic]] as seperate groups. Similarities noted between the two groups include the accusative case ending and pronominal stems.